cs.HC, cs.SD, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.CL

This paper focuses on the design and analysis of a touchscreen app for social musical interaction, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM). The app also collects data on user interactions and musical outputs, which can be analysed using data science techniques (cs.SD). The paper discusses the affordances and constraints of mobile devices for musical performance, which relates to social impact (cs.SI). Finally, the paper provides design recommendations for touchscreen apps, which could involve natural language processing and machine learning (cs.CL).
